articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

articleContent.title: Step up your stay at Radisson Blu: the style-savvy hotels travelers adore

seoInfo.metaDescription: If you’re the kind of traveler who carefully curates a wish list for each trip, you deserve a stay that lives up to it. With a focus on premium amenities, inspired menus, and striking interiors, Radisson Blu hotels offer memorable experiences in unmissable destinations throughout North and South America.* Discover all there is to love about Radisson Blu in this roundup of top-rated stays.

tripContent.title: Santa Fe: heritage & history on the Original Route 66
tripContent.description: Looking for adventure on the original Route 66? Santa Fe, the oldest state capital, is a must-stop for history buffs. The city, founded in 1610, is older than the United States—but the area has been populated for well over a thousand years. With so much history and heritage, you'll want to allow plenty of time to explore the best of the Southwest—so here are 12 suggestions for things to see, do, and learn.

articleContent.title: How to plan the perfect road trip in coastal Maine

seoInfo.metaDescription: Cory Lee takes us on an accessible tour of Acadia National Park, Ogunquit, and beyond.

You can definitely get a taste of all Madrid has to offer in two days, and I should know. I've spent plenty of time exploring Spain's capital city, indulging in wine-filled afternoons, late-night tapas, and showstopping flamenco—all in a day's work. Sure, you'll probably wish you had more time (you might need a lifetime to study the city's sweeping Spanish and Latin American art collection) but you can do a lot of living here in 48 hours.

tripContent.title: Experience Santa Fe: art, flavor & fun on the Original Route 66
tripContent.description: Whether you enjoy nature hikes or margarita trails (or both!), you'll want to embrace everything Santa Fe has to offer. Its unique mix of big-city culture, small-town charm, and Southwestern flavor has earned it the nickname "The City Different." Whatever you're into—from art to opera to world-class restaurants—Santa Fe offers a chance to escape the everyday.

tripContent.title: Celebrate Nevada's history, rhythm, and culture
tripContent.description: Nevada’s story is etched in historic mining towns, roadside wonders, galleries, and museums. From frontier heritage and atomic relics to glowing neon art, every stop reveals a new layer of the state's past and present. Whether you're wandering small-town streets or stepping into iconic city museums, this journey blends memory and motion in a way that’s anything but ordinary.
